  "doc_id": "32038",
  "text": "GLUT6 (SLC2A6, formerly referred to as GLUT9) was first cloned from human leukocytes using the conserved 'hexose transporter signatures' in expressed sequence tag (EST) databases [CITATION_1] . It was found to be expressed mainly in the brain, spleen, and peripheral leucocytes. Hexose transport for GLUT6 was demonstrated in reconstituted liposomes, where GLUT6 transport activity was found only in the presence of 5 mM but not 1 mM glucose and exhibited a low cytochalasin B binding affinity [CITATION_2] .",
